g801.definition: [ἀσύνετος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g4908}}; unintelligent; by implication, wicked

g802.definition: [ἀσύνθετος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g4934}}; properly, not agreed, i.e. treacherous to compacts

g804.definition: [ἀσφαλής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and sphallo (to "fail"); secure (literally or figuratively)

g808.definition: [ἀσχημοσύνη] from {{g809}}; an indecency; by implication, the pudenda

g809.definition: [ἀσχήμων] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g2192}} (in the sense of its congener {{g4976}}); properly, shapeless, i.e. (figuratively) inelegant

g810.definition: [ἀσωτία] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g4982}}; properly, unsavedness, i.e. (by implication) profligacy

g811.definition: [ἀσώτως] adverb from the same as {{g810}}; dissolutely

g813.definition: [ἄτακτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g5021}}; unarranged, i.e. (by implication) insubordinate (religiously)

g815.definition: [ἄτεκνος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5043}}; childless

g816.definition: [ἀτενίζω] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a particle of union) and τείνω (to stretch); to gaze intently

g817.definition: [ἄτερ] a particle probably akin to {{g427}}; aloof, i.e. apart from (literally or figuratively)

g818.definition: [ἀτιμάζω] from {{g820}}; to render infamous, i.e. (by implication) contemn or maltreat

g819.definition: [ἀτιμία] from {{g820}}; infamy, i.e. (subjectively) comparative indignity, (objectively) disgrace

g820.definition: [ἄτιμος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5092}}; (negatively) unhonoured or (positively) dishonoured

g823.definition: [ἄτομος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and the base of {{g5114}}; uncut, i.e. (by implication) indivisible (an "atom" of time)

g824.definition: [ἄτοπος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5117}}; out of place, i.e. (figuratively) improper, injurious, wicked

g825.definition: [Ἀττάλεια] from Ἄτταλος (a king of Pergamus); Attaleia, a place in Pamphylia

g827.definition: [αὐγή] of uncertain derivation; a ray of light, i.e. (by implication) radiance, dawn

g828.definition: [Αὐγοῦστος] from Latin (""); Augustus, a title of the Roman emperor

g829.definition: [αὐθάδης] from {{g846}} and the base of {{g2237}}; self-pleasing, i.e. arrogant

g830.definition: [αὐθαίρετος] from {{g846}} and the same as {{g140}}; self-chosen, i.e. (by implication) voluntary

g831.definition: [αὐθεντέω] from a compound of {{g846}} and an obsolete ἕντης (a worker); to act of oneself, i.e. (figuratively) dominate

g833.definition: [αὐλή] from the same as {{g109}}; a yard (as open to the wind); by implication, a mansion

g835.definition: [αὐλίζομαι] middle voice from {{g833}}; to pass the night (properly, in the open air)

g836.definition: [αὐλός] from the same as {{g109}}; a flute (as blown)

g837.definition: [αὐξάνω] a prolonged form of a primary verb; to grow ("wax"), i.e. enlarge (literal or figurative, active or passive)

g839.definition: [αὔριον] from a derivative of the same as {{g109}} (meaning a breeze, i.e. the morning air); properly, fresh, i.e. (adverb with ellipsis of {{g2250}}) to-morrow

g840.definition: [αὐστηρός] from a (presumed) derivative of the same as {{g109}} (meaning blown); rough (properly as a gale), i.e. (figuratively) severe

g841.definition: [αὐτάρκεια] from {{g842}}; self-satisfaction, i.e. (abstractly) contentedness, or (concretely) a competence

g843.definition: [αὐτοκατάκριτος] from {{g846}} and a derivative or {{g2632}}; self-condemned

g844.definition: [αὐτόματος] from {{g846}} and the same as {{g3155}}; self-moved ("automatic"), i.e. spontaneous

g845.definition: [αὐτόπτης] from {{g846}} and {{g3700}}; self-seeing, i.e. an eye-witness

g846.definition: [αὐτός] from the particle αὖ (perhaps akin to the base of {{g109}} through the idea of a baffling wind) (backward); the reflexive pronoun self, used (alone or in the comparative {{g1438}}) of the third person , and (with the proper personal pronoun) of the other persons Compare {{g848}}.

g847.definition: [αὐτοῦ] genitive (i.e. possessive) of {{g846}}, used as an adverb of location; properly, belonging to the same spot, i.e. in this (or that) place

g848.definition: [αὑτοῦ] contracted for {{g1438}}; self (in some oblique case or reflexive relation)

g849.definition: [αὐτόχειρ] from {{g846}} and {{g5495}}; self-handed, i.e. doing personally

g850.definition: [αὐχμηρός] from αὐχμός (probably from a base akin to that of {{g109}}) (dust, as dried by wind); properly, dirty, i.e. (by implication) obscure

g851.definition: [ἀφαιρέω] from {{g575}} and {{g138}}; to remove (literally or figuratively)

g852.definition: [ἀφανής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5316}}; non-apparent

g853.definition: [ἀφανίζω] from {{g852}}; to render unapparent, i.e. (actively) consume (becloud), or (passively) disappear (be destroyed)

g855.definition: [ἄφαντος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g5316}}; non-manifested, i.e. invisible

g856.definition: [ἀφεδρών] from a compound of {{g575}} and the base of {{g1476}}; a place of sitting apart, i.e. a privy

g857.definition: [ἀφειδία] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5339}}; unsparingness, i.e. austerity (asceticism)

g858.definition: [ἀφελότης] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and φέλλος (in the sense of a stone as stubbing the foot); smoothness, i.e. (figuratively) simplicity

g861.definition: [ἀφθαρσία] from {{g862}}; incorruptibility; genitive, unending existence; (figuratively) genuineness

g862.definition: [ἄφθαρτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g5351}}; undecaying (in essence or continuance)

g863.definition: [ἀφίημι] from {{g575}} and ἵημι (to send; an intensive form of εἶμι, to go); to send forth, in various applications (as follow)

g864.definition: [ἀφικνέομαι] from {{g575}} and the base of {{g2425}}; to go (i.e. spread) forth (by rumor)

g865.definition: [ἀφιλάγαθος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5358}}; hostile to virtue

g866.definition: [ἀφιλάργυρος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5366}}; unavaricious

g867.definition: [ἄφιξις] from {{g864}}; properly, arrival, i.e. (by implication) departure

g868.definition: [ἀφίστημι] from {{g575}} and {{g2476}}; to remove, i.e. (actively) instigate to revolt; usually (reflexively) to desist, desert, etc.

g870.definition: [ἀφόβως] adverb from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5401}}; fearlessly

g873.definition: [ἀφορίζω] from {{g575}} and {{g3724}}; to set off by boundary, i.e. (figuratively) limit, exclude, appoint, etc.

g874.definition: [ἀφορμή] from a compound of {{g575}} and {{g3729}}; a starting-point, i.e. (figuratively) an opportunity

g875.definition: [ἀφρίζω] from {{g876}}; to froth at the mouth (in epilepsy)

g876.definition: [ἀφρός] apparently a primary word; froth, i.e. slaver

g878.definition: [ἄφρων] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5424}}; properly, mindless, i.e. stupid, (by implication) ignorant, (specially) egotistic, (practically) rash, or (morally) unbelieving

g879.definition: [ἀφυπνόω] from a compound of {{g575}} and {{g5258}}; properly, to become awake, i.e. (by implication) to drop (off) in slumber

g880.definition: [ἄφωνος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5456}}; voiceless, i.e. mute (by nature or choice); figuratively, unmeaning

g881.definition: [Ἀχάζ] of Hebrew origin ({{h271}}); Achaz, an Israelite

g882.definition: [Ἀχαΐα] of uncertain derivation; Achaia (i.e. Greece), a country of Europe

g883.definition: [Ἀχαϊκός] from {{g882}}; an Achaian; Achaicus, a Christian

g884.definition: [ἀχάριστος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g5483}}; thankless, i.e. ungrateful

g885.definition: [Ἀχείμ] probably of Hebrew origin (compare {{h3137}}); Achim, an Israelite

g886.definition: [ἀχειροποίητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5499}}; unmanufactured, i.e. inartificial

g887.definition: [ἀχλύς] of uncertain derivation; dimness of sight, i.e. (probably) a cataract

g888.definition: [ἀχρεῖος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g5534}} (compare {{g5532}}); useless, i.e. (euphemistically) unmeritorious

g889.definition: [ἀχρειόω] from {{g888}}; to render useless, i.e. spoil

g890.definition: [ἄχρηστος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5543}}; inefficient, i.e. (by implication) detrimental

g891.definition: [ἄχρι]   or ἄχρις; akin to {{g206}} (through the idea of a terminus); (of time) until or (of place) up to Compare {{g3360}}.

g892.definition: [ἄχυρον] perhaps remotely from χέω (to shed forth); chaff (as diffusive)

g893.definition: [ἀψευδής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5579}}; veracious

g894.definition: [ἄψινθος] of uncertain derivation; wormwood (as a type of bitterness, i.e. (figuratively) calamity)

g895.definition: [ἄψυχος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5590}}; lifeless, i.e. inanimate (mechanical)

g896.definition: [Βάαλ] of Hebrew origin ({{h1168}}); Baal, a Phœnician deity (used as a symbol of idolatry)

g897.definition: [Βαβυλών] of Hebrew origin ({{h894}}); Babylon, the capitol of Chaldæa (literally or figuratively (as a type of tyranny))

g898.definition: [βαθμός] from the same as {{g899}}; a step, i.e. (figuratively) grade (of dignity)

g899.definition: [βάθος] from the same as {{g901}}; profundity, i.e. (by implication) extent; (figuratively) mystery
